Foldercrypt is a encrypted folder management tool.
This the Ubuntu Google Summer of Code project of Kévin Dunglas,
mentored by Jani Monoses.

See http://code.google.com/p/foldercrypt/ for details.
Informations about Ubuntu Linux: http://www.ubuntu.com
Informations about Google Summer of Code: http://code.google.com/soc/


!!! READ THIS BEFORE ANY USE !!!
================================
This is a BETA software pulished ONLY FOR TEST !
It can DESTROY your data.
Test it only on BACKUPED directories.

Please send us report using our issues tracker at code.google.com. Don't forget
to attach the traceback (everything displayed in the terminal window).


INSTALL
=======
Depends of:
- Python 2.5
- encfs (apt-get install encfs)

To use foldercrypt-gtk you need:
- gtk
- pygtk.glade Python modules (provided by PyGTK)

To use the nautilus extension you need:
- nautilus
- nautilus-python (apt-get install nautilus-python python)-dev

To use folercrypt-kde you need:
- KDE Python bindings
- libpythonize
- PyKDE extensions

To install a component just go into his directory and type as root:
# python setup.py install


FOLDERCRYPT
=============
Command: foldercrypt

Options:
--crypt DIRECTORY       encrypt directory
--open DIRECTORY        open an encrypted folder
--help                  display this help message
--close DIRECTORY       close an encrypted folder
--decrypt DIRECTORY     decrypt encrypted folder
--version               display version information


Examples :

# Create some samples
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ mkdir test
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ echo "Bonjour" > test/bonjour
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ echo "Aurevoir" > test/aurevoir

# Encrypt a directory
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ./foldercrypt --crypt test
Password: azerty

[...]

# List the content of the directory unmounted
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ls test

# Open the encrypted directory
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ./foldercrypt --open test
Password: azerty

# List the content of the mounted encrypted directory
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ls test
aurevoir  bonjour  lost+found

# Close it
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ./foldercrypt --close test
# List if content
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ls test

# Decrypt it
dunglas@kirk:~/Projects/foldercrypt$ ./foldercrypt --decrypt test
Password: azerty
aurevoir  bonjour  lost+found
